'North East England' is one of the nine regions of England that are classified
at the first level of NUTS for statistical purposes. It covers Northumberland,
County Durham, Tyne and Wear, and Teesside, which is partly in North Yorkshire.
The largest urban area in the region is Tyneside. The only cities in the North
East are Durham, Newcastle upon Tyne and Sunderland. Other large settlements in
the region include Darlington; Gateshead; Hartlepool; Middlesbrough; Redcar;
South Shields and Stockton-on-Tees. The region is home to three large
conurbations: Teesside, Wearside, and Tyneside, which is the largest of the
three and the sixth most populous conurbation in the United Kingdom.
